menu "bb_cache"

config BB_CACHE_MAX_TOPICS
    int "Maximum number of registered cache topics"
    default 32
    range 1 64
    help
        Fixed-size registry capacity. Each entry holds a fixed-size key
        buffer, optional owned struct buffer, serializer fn, and a mutex.
        Increase if more than 8 state topics need caching.

config BB_CACHE_KEY_MAX
    int "Maximum length of a registered cache key (bytes, incl. NUL)"
    default 96
    range 8 256
    help
        Fixed-size per-entry key buffer. bb_cache_register() copies the
        caller's key into this buffer (the caller no longer needs to keep
        the string alive) and rejects keys of length >= this value with
        BB_ERR_INVALID_ARG. The default (96) matches bb_sub's own ingress
        topic cap (BB_SUB_TOPIC_MAX) so every dynamically-routed MQTT topic
        bb_sub registers fits; static breadboard keys (e.g.
        "update.available") are far shorter. Standing cost is
        BB_CACHE_KEY_MAX * BB_CACHE_MAX_TOPICS bytes.

endmenu
